{%- comment -%}
  Reamaze defer placeholder — bd hairmnl-theme-meu.2 (Phase 3 of epic meu).

  Server-rendered chat bubble that visually matches the live Reamaze widget
  configured in admin (widgetColor=rgb(102,90,68), gradient=true, desktop
  bottom:80px right:22px, mobile bottom:50px right:16px). Clickable from
  first paint — the guard inline in layout/theme.liquid listens for clicks
  on #reamaze-defer-placeholder and triggers SDK load.

  Once Reamaze SDK paints its own widget, the guard sets [hidden] on this
  button so the two never co-exist visually.

  kt0 compliance (CLAUDE.md): uses position:fixed only. No contain, no
  transform, no filter — those would create containing blocks for any
  absolute-positioned descendants of the bubble (per 2026-05-12 7fz
  regression history).
{%- endcomment -%}
<button
  type="button"
  id="reamaze-defer-placeholder"
  aria-label="Open chat support"
>
  <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" width="28" height="28">
    <path fill="#fff" d="M12 2C6.48 2 2 6.13 2 11.2c0 2.83 1.4 5.36 3.62 7.08L5 22l3.96-1.72C10.06 20.74 11.02 21 12 21c5.52 0 10-4.13 10-9.8S17.52 2 12 2z"/>
  </svg>
</button>
<style>
  #reamaze-defer-placeholder {
    position: fixed;
    bottom: 80px;
    right: 22px;
    width: 60px;
    height: 60px;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgb(102, 90, 68) 0%, rgb(128, 113, 85) 100%);
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
    cursor: pointer;
    z-index: 9998;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }
  @media (max-width: 767px) {
    #reamaze-defer-placeholder {
      bottom: 50px;
      right: 16px;
    }
  }
  #reamaze-defer-placeholder svg,
  #reamaze-defer-placeholder svg * {
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  #reamaze-defer-placeholder[hidden] {
    display: none !important;
  }
</style>
